claim.claim-text:
1. A light-emitting element comprising:
an anode;
a first layer over and in contact with the anode, the first layer comprising a first organic compound;
an organic compound layer over and in contact with the first layer;
a second layer over and in contact with the organic compound layer, the second layer comprising the first organic compound; and
a cathode over and in contact with the second layer,
wherein:
the organic compound layer comprises a first region and a light-emitting region over and in contact with the first region;
the first region comprises the first organic compound and a hole-trapping substance; and
the light-emitting region comprises the first organic compound and a light-emitting substance.

9. A light-emitting element comprising:
an anode;
a first layer over and in contact with the anode, the first layer comprising an N-type region in contact with the anode and a P-type region over and in contact with the N-type region;
an organic compound layer over and in contact with the first layer, the organic compound layer comprising a first organic compound;
a second layer over and in contact with the organic compound layer, the second layer comprising the first organic compound; and
a cathode over and in contact with the second layer,
wherein:
the N-type region comprises the first organic compound and an electron-donating substance;
the P-type region comprises the first organic compound and an electron-accepting substance;
the organic compound layer comprises a first region and a light-emitting region over and in contact with the first region;
the first region comprises the first organic compound and a hole-trapping substance; and
the light-emitting region comprises the first organic compound and a light-emitting substance.

16. A light-emitting element comprising:
an anode;
a first layer over and in contact with the anode, the first layer comprising a first organic compound;
an organic compound layer over and in contact with the first layer; and
a second layer over and in contact with the organic compound layer, the second layer comprising an N-type region and a P-type region over and in contact with the N-type region; and
a cathode over and in contact with the second layer,
wherein:
the N-type region comprises the first organic compound and an electron-donating substance;
the P-type region comprises the first organic compound and an electron-accepting substance;
the organic compound layer comprises a first region and a light-emitting region over and in contact with the first region;
the first region comprises the first organic compound and a hole-trapping substance; and
the light-emitting region comprises the first organic compound and a light-emitting substance.
